What is unique about the personal online data warehouse is that it is up to the user alone to decide who has access to what kind of information.
The company calls it "personal data empowerment".
The idea of Inrupt, according to the company's CEO John Bruce, is to provide the proper resources, processes and skills to help make Solid available to everyone.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, a few in-house programmers hired to work on the project, and a community of volunteer programmers.
