2004: On 26 December a strong earthquake on the western coast of Indonesia's Aceh province in northern Sumatra caused a tsunami that hit 14 countries, killing 226,000 people along the Indian Ocean coast, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of strong earthquakes hit the western coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
